<h4>
  Upward motion only
</h4>

<p>
  Many pop-up problems deal only with flying upward, and ignore the downward motion.
  Two questions like this are:
  "How high does an object rise?"
  and "How long does it take the object to reach its highest point?"
  The following concepts can
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    If a question asks "How high does an object rise?",
    you are looking for vertical displacement.
  </li>
  <li>
    If a question asks "How long does it take to reach its highest point?",
    you are looking for change in time.
  </li>
  <li>
    At the very top of the motion, the object momentarily has velocity zero.
    So if you are analyzing motion from the moment it is thrown upward
    to the top, the final velocity is equal to zero!
  </li>
</ul>

